5000|$|... • Based on {{preliminary}} results, {{the natural}} geological {{setting of the}} oil field was deemed to be highly suitable for long-term <b>CO2</b> geological <b>storage</b> • The results form the most complete, comprehensive, peer-reviewed data set {{in the world for}} <b>CO2</b> geological <b>storage.</b> However, additional research was deemed to be needed to further develop and refine CO2 monitoring and verification technologies. With this in mind a second, and final phase of research was developed and began in the year 2005, and will be completed in 2011.The PTRC and IEA GHG issued a full report on the first phase, and it is available from the PTRC’s website.|$|R
