2500|$|Unminable coal seams {{can be used}} {{to store}} CO2, because CO2 absorbs to the coal surface, {{ensuring}} safe long-term storage. [...] In the process it releases methane that was previously adsorbed to the coal surface and that may be recovered. [...] Again the sale of the methane {{can be used to}} offset the cost of the <b>CO2</b> <b>storage.</b> Release or burning of methane would of course at least partially offset the obtained sequestration result – except when the gas is allowed to escape into the atmosphere in significant quantities: methane has a higher global warming potential than CO2.|$|E
